criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age > 18 years;

          -  a clear history of RAS (recurrent apthous stomatitis) occurring no less than four
             times a year;

          -  presentation with one or two ulcers measuring 10 mm in diameter for 48 hours and yet
             to receive treatment;

          -  ulcers that took > 5 days to resolve without treatment.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  had underlying systemic disease(s) or a history of immunologic disorder(s);

          -  were taking immunomodulatory agents or systemic nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs <
             1 month before study commencement;

          -  are smokers;

          -  are pregnant;

          -  had a history of abusing drugs or alcohol;

          -  could not provide written informed consent
